</div></div><div class="sqs-block html-block sqs-block-html" data-block-type="2" id="block-67213a857182bd23b316"><div class="sqs-block-content">

<div class="sqs-html-content">
  <p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">On Sunday 4th December, from 12-4pm, the High Street will be transformed into a winter wonderland of festive fun. The High Street shops will be opening their doors for you to find gifts galore to suit all tastes and budgets. </p><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">Alongside the shops, there will be a variety of stalls featuring crafts, books &amp; local produce. The pubs and restaurants along the High Street will be keeping you fuelled, offering goodies such as pulled pork baps, chilli, cold beers, boozy hot chocolate, and of course, that most festive of tipples – mulled wine. </p><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">Entertainment will be provided by the Straw Dogs, DJ Em will be doing her thing on the green and Zoe at Creative Spaces will be putting on a show at the <a href="https://hurstplayers.org.uk" target="_blank">Players Theatre</a>. And for a special festive treat, the <a href="https://www.holytrinityhpp.org" target="_blank">Holy Trinity church</a> choir will be performing some favourite carols. And for the little ones, there will be face painting, balloon modelling, a nativity photo booth, and an appearance from the big man himself – Father Christmas. Wrap up warm and join us for the festivities, Sunday 4th December 12pm-4pm.</p>
</div>



</div></div></div></div></div></div>
        
      
